- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is likely because the paper presents a verification strategy based on equational theory and algebraic laws. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely because the paper deals with reactive programs and their semantics. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possibility because the paper discusses practical verification support. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant because the paper uses Kleene algebra to reason about iterative programs with reactive invariants. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is a possibility because the paper describes the mechanisation of the laws and strategy in Isabelle/UTP.
